sect2.para:
Access Control A category can be public or private;
Public: Any body can view a public category and any user can add events to it. However users will only be able to see the events 					inside the category to which they have access to.
Private: Only those users in the access list or administrators can access the category and add events. When a Category is made 					private, the option for domain control is omitted and any event or category made inside will also be private. The category will be 				displayed with "(protected)" after its name to show it is private.
